The word '''lime''' may refer to:

*Powdered [[chalk]] or [[limestone]], consisting primarily of [[calcium carbonate]], and often with [[calcium oxide]], [[magnesium carbonate]], or [[magnesium oxide]], used in as a [[soil additive]] in [[agriculture]]  to increase the [[pH]] (reduce the [[acidity]]) of [[soil]]. 

*[[Calcium oxide]] ("burnt lime" or "quicklime")

*Various trees of the genus ''Citrus'' (especially  ''Citrus latifolia'') or their sour green or yellow fruits. See [[Lime (fruit)]].

